# Hydra Kernel — Governance Enforcement Layer (GEL)
**Component:** C1  
**Version:** 0.8.1  
**Status:** Governance path and APP route are live. FM1 + minimal SLM path integrated via ModelClient. FM2/review/archive remain pending.
 
---
 
## What This Is
 
The GEL is a TypeScript Express server that acts as a governed HTTP proxy between clients and OpenClaw. Every request is intercepted by the Governance Plane before it can reach any Cognitive Node (model/skill).
 
**Default behaviour: DENY ALL.** Nothing passes through until a policy explicitly allows it.
 
---
 
## Architecture
 
```
Client → GEL :3100 → [Governance Plane]
                          ↓ DENY  → 403 response
                          ↓ ALLOW → handler (APP pipeline lane)
                                  → OpenClaw :3000 (proxy path)
 
OpenClaw :3000 → [Model Inference Gateway — Component C6]
                          ↓ DLC token check (stub — not yet enforced)
                          ↓ real model API call (stub — not yet wired)
                          ↓ response with liability chain headers
```
 
**GEL decides. OpenClaw executes. Never the same component (Invariant 9).**
 
> ⚠️ Direct access to port 3000 bypasses all governance. In production, firewall :3000.
 
