## Digital Library Card (DLC)
 
The DLC is the authentication layer that makes the VCKB marketplace work at scale.
 
It is a **three-component cryptographic credential** — one token that simultaneously:
 
| Component | Analogy | Contains |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| **AI Model Signature** | Routing number | Model identity, version, governance profile, liability |
| **Personal Signature** | Account number | User identity, VCKB permissions, micropayment rails |
| **Entity Signature** | The bank itself | Institution, licensed modules, liability ceiling |
 
**What one DLC token authorizes:**
- Proves who you are (personal)
- Proves what AI you're using and its governance profile (model)
- Proves what entity you're affiliated with and what modules they've licensed (institutional)
- Authorizes micropayment rails — VCKB author compensation per retrieval, automatic
- Opens paywalled content without a separate handshake per request
- Opens locally stored password-protected files (same token works on-network and local)
- Tracks usage at token level for author compensation calculation
- Establishes full liability chain: `personal → institutional → model → content author`
 
**Without DLC:** Every VCKB retrieval requires 5 round trips (auth, verify, pay, log, liability).  
**With DLC:** All five collapse into one cryptographic operation.
 
**Status:** Stub hooks live in `current/openclaw/src/index.ts` → `validateDLCToken()`.  
Not yet enforced. Next build: implement token generation in personal AI Space + verify here.
 
---
 
## Architectural Invariants Enforced
 
- **Invariant 3**: Governance Plane decides independently — does not ask the model
- **Invariant 6**: Envelopes generated for all allowed requests
- **Invariant 8**: Default DENY — fail closed under ambiguity
- **Invariant 9**: GEL decides; OpenClaw executes — never the same component
- **Invariant 11**: All interceptions, decisions, and errors logged — no silent degradation
 
---
 
