# OpenClaw — What It Is and How GEL Connects to It
 
**This folder contains setup configuration for OpenClaw.**  
**OpenClaw is NOT included in this zip. It is installed separately.**
 
---
 
## What OpenClaw Actually Is
 
OpenClaw (formerly Clawdbot/Moltbot) is an open-source, local-first AI agent framework.
 
- GitHub: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw
- License: MIT — free to use, fork, and modify
- Install: `npm install -g openclaw`
- Stars: ~64k (as of March 2026)
 
It is NOT a simple inference server. It is a full AI agent system that:
- Runs a Gateway daemon on your machine (default port :3000)
- Connects to any LLM provider: Anthropic, OpenAI, Groq, Ollama, LM Studio, etc.
- Has persistent memory, skills system, multi-channel support (Telegram, Discord, etc.)
- Stores conversations and config as plain Markdown and YAML — fully inspectable
- Supports local model inference via Ollama or LM Studio (no API key needed)
 
---
 
## Why GEL Proxies to OpenClaw
 
The relationship:
 
```
Client request
     ↓
GEL :3100  ← YOU ARE HERE (this repo)
[Governance Plane]
  Policy evaluation
  Execution envelope generation
  Telemetry logging
  Replay capability
     ↓ ALLOW
OpenClaw Gateway :3000  ← OPENCLAW (installed separately)
[Agent Layer]
  Model provider selection
  Memory and context
  Skills execution
  LLM API calls
     ↓
LLM Provider (Anthropic / OpenAI / Groq / local)
```
 
GEL = the cage and the audit trail.  
OpenClaw = the agent that executes inside the cage.
 
This is Architectural Invariant 9 in practice:
- GEL decides what is permitted (policy → envelope → enforcement)
- OpenClaw executes what GEL has authorized
- They are never the same component
 
---
 
## Installing OpenClaw
 
```bash
# Install globally
npm install -g openclaw
 
# Or from source
git clone https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw.git
cd openclaw
pnpm install
pnpm build
 
# First-time setup (interactive onboarding)
openclaw onboard
```
 
OpenClaw's gateway will start on :3000 by default.  
The GEL is already configured to proxy to `http://localhost:3000`.
 
---
 
## Configuring OpenClaw to Work with GEL
 
The key requirement: OpenClaw needs at least one model provider configured.
 
**Option A — Anthropic API (recommended for FM1)**
 
```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
 
Set your key: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...` in OpenClaw's `.env`
 
**Option B — Groq (fast, cheap, good for SLM layer)**
 
```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "groq/llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
        "fallbacks": ["anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```
 
Set: `GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...`
 
**Option C — Local via Ollama (no API key, runs on your machine)**
 
```bash
# Install Ollama: https://ollama.ai
ollama pull llama3.3
# Ollama auto-detected at http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1
```
 
```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "ollama/llama3.3"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
 
No API key required. Hardware dependent — needs decent GPU or CPU.
 
---
 
## OpenClaw Config for This Project (`openclaw.json`)
 
Place this in your OpenClaw workspace:
 
```json
{
