  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"problemStatement": "Hospital staff keep skipping hand-washing protocols despite repeated training."}'
```
 
---
 
## Cost-Free Option for Development
 
Groq offers very fast, very cheap inference on Llama models.  
For the SLM layer (parallel substrate modification suggesters), Groq is ideal:
- Near-zero cost for 5-10 parallel small calls
- Fast enough to run in parallel without waiting
- Tool calling supported
 
For FM1 (Pattern Mapper) and FM2 (Scorer), Anthropic's Claude is preferred  
because it needs to deeply reason from the VCKB documents.
 
The demo can run with:
- FM1: Anthropic Claude Sonnet ($0.003 per 1K tokens input, ~$0.01-0.05 per problem)
- SLMs: Groq Llama (~$0.0001 per call × 5-10 calls = negligible)
- FM2: Anthropic Claude Sonnet (same as FM1)
- Total per demo run: under $0.25
 
